SAM: Secrets are the best. You ma'am.

00:33:44.448 --> 00:33:49.827
AUDIENCE MEMBER: I know I asked all of you
yesterday, but I'm really interesting in voice

00:33:49.827 --> 00:33:57.688
acting, and you said theater, theater, theater.
Are there any good online resources? Either forums

00:33:57.688 --> 00:34:02.857
you can do, or other resources?

00:34:02.857 --> 00:34:06.598
MATT: A good website you can go to for an overall
view of the industry and getting into it is

00:34:06.598 --> 00:34:10.677
iwanttobeavoiceactor.com, run by Dee Bradley
Baker, one of the most prolific

00:34:10.677 --> 00:34:12.449
voice actors in the industry.

00:34:12.449 --> 00:34:13.946
LAURA: He is amazing.

00:34:13.946 --> 00:34:16.678
MATT: So that's a really good place to start.
There aren't that many people out there who can do

00:34:16.678 --> 00:34:20.138
online workshops and classes with you. Just make
sure that anyone who's offering you a class, you

00:34:20.138 --> 00:34:25.887
research their work and see that one: they're
reputable, two: they are working in the industry,

00:34:25.887 --> 00:34:28.537
and three: that they're not charging way too
much.

00:34:28.537 --> 00:34:31.757
LAURA: Because there are a lot of people who don't
actually work very much that will do classes and

00:34:31.757 --> 00:34:34.408
you won't learn very much.

00:34:34.408 --> 00:34:39.157
AUDIENCE MEMBER: So what's a good portfolio to
look at to get examples from?

00:34:39.157 --> 00:34:41.217
TRAVIS: Just a crap load of credits.

00:34:41.217 --> 00:34:46.856
